<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="sharp-adj">sharp <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ʃɑːp/    美 /ʃɑːrp/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>锋利的；尖的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>sharp teeth
锋利的牙齿</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(角度、变化等) 急剧的；明显的</strong></h4>
<p>sudden and rapid, especially of a change：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a sharp bend
急转弯</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a sharp drop / increase in prices 
价格急剧下跌/上涨</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>(感观) 敏锐的；(人) 机灵的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 dull / stupid </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She has <strong>sharp eyes</strong>.
她目光敏锐。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a sharp child
机灵的孩子</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>(言辞等) 尖刻的；严厉的</strong></h4>
<p>(of a person or what they say) critical or severe：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>sharp criticism
尖锐的批评</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>be sharp with</strong> sb
对某人严厉</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.★ <strong>剧烈的；猛烈的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I felt a sharp pain in my back.
我感到背上一阵剧痛。</p></div>

<h4 id="6">6.★ <strong>尖厉的；刺耳的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Through all the noise came a sharp warning cry.
嘈杂中传来一声尖锐的警告声。</p><footer>2014 重庆</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>sharply /'ʃɑːpli/ adv <br />
1. <strong>急剧地；严厉地：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>House prices have risen sharply over the last decade.
过去十年里房价急剧上涨。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>speak sharply to sb 
斥责某人</p></div>

<p>sharpen  v <br />
1. <strong>削尖；磨快</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>sharpen a pencil
削铅笔</p></div>

<ol>
<li><strong>使提高；使改进</strong>  </li>
</ol>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Debates sharpen one’s wits.
辩论增长才智。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Hardly had Sabrina finished her words when Albert said <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (sharp), “Don’t be so mean,” pointing a finger of warning at her.  （2014 湖北改）  </li>
<li>Nowadays, there is a <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (急剧的) increase in children’s creativity, for they are greatly encouraged to develop their talents.    （2011 福建改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. sharply  2. sharp  </p></div>